в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ          в–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳ       в–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳ

Agents and humans can both concurrently connect to miscreant and use it
to coordinate and resolve conflicts. All git objects (trees, commits, blob IDs)
are stored in SlateDB as well as any blob content that is under a certain
threshold (64KB default) while all blobs that exceed this threshold are stored
directly in S3. The blobs and the slatedb directories are stored within the same
S3 bucket.

> Note that S3 is a placeholder for any object storage system, we could use
> GCS, R2, Tigris, etc...

